<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   Improved Natural Durability - Each skill level increases the character's natural hit points (hit point total without any buffs or magic items). The first skill level increases the character's HPs by 2%, the second skill level by 5% and the third skill level by 10%.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Now, that CLEARLY says that buffs and gear are not included. And it does not distinguish between items that give +Stamina and items that give +HPs either. I can understand the logical behind that but again, I'm reading this to say &quot;natural&quot; only and to me, natural does not include gear.<br>
<br>
